QueryText: Manure and fertilizer in mango plants ?
KCCAns: One year after planting the garden, 200 gm urea per plant, 300 gram single super phosphate, 200 g potassium sulphate and 25 kg. Drying of cow dung should be added to the soil in the plate made around the tree in July. Nitrogen, potash and phosphorus should be provided in the coefficient of the year every year till the age of ten years. If it is a ten year tree, this quantity is 2.0 kg urea, 3.0 kg single super phosphate, 2.0 kg potassium sulphate and 25 kg. Dung mustard manure should be done. After ten years, this quantity should be adjusted and after this, give this amount every year. After the flowering of the mango tree and before the fruit is formed, make a solution in the multiplex 3-4 ml / liters of water.
